value.0: Oh, it must be my father, Janken! He must be worried sick about me.
I don't know where the little one went, Orlane's his name, but I know that the pretty elf, Terari, was going to try his charms on the sirines. You could go ask him.

The Spirit is normally peaceful and comes into the Wood through its grove to tend to the creatures. Since the violence began, the Spirit hasn't come through at all. If it had, I would have tried to talk to it.
The grove is some kind of entrance to another realm where the Spirit usually lives. I haven't the slightest idea what the other realm looks like though.
I don't know much about the grove, mostly just stories. I do know that no living creature can get through the portal and into the other realm.
Now that you have freed me, I will return to the camp and consult with the other druids about the Spirit of the Wood.
I can make it on my own. I will meet up with you at the druid encampment.
Not specifically. Are you one of them?
Tell me more about this grove.
